<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="170" pageId="17" pageNumber="169" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,150,465]" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,222,248]" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female (
<figureCitation box="[428,511,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–79" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,495,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-164@17.[151,1436,489,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 71–79. Meria sanguinicollis, 71, 73, 76–77, ♀; 72, 74–75, 78–79, ♂. 71–72. Habitus, dorsal view; 73. Head, frontal view; 74. Head, ventral view; 75. Pronotum, lateral view; 76. Propodeum, dorsal view; 77. Metasoma, dorsal view; 78. T3–T5, dorsal view; 79. T7, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646969/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
). Head 1.2× wider than high in frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[1030,1115,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–79" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,495,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-164@17.[151,1436,489,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 71–79. Meria sanguinicollis, 71, 73, 76–77, ♀; 72, 74–75, 78–79, ♂. 71–72. Habitus, dorsal view; 73. Head, frontal view; 74. Head, ventral view; 75. Pronotum, lateral view; 76. Propodeum, dorsal view; 77. Metasoma, dorsal view; 78. T3–T5, dorsal view; 79. T7, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646969/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
); anterior margin of clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[160,242,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–79" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,495,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-164@17.[151,1436,489,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 71–79. Meria sanguinicollis, 71, 73, 76–77, ♀; 72, 74–75, 78–79, ♂. 71–72. Habitus, dorsal view; 73. Head, frontal view; 74. Head, ventral view; 75. Pronotum, lateral view; 76. Propodeum, dorsal view; 77. Metasoma, dorsal view; 78. T3–T5, dorsal view; 79. T7, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646969/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
) rounded; genal bridge absent; OOD: POD = 1; pronotum sometimes red and only anteriorly with a few dense punctures, and width of posterior margin 1.4× length of anterior to posterior margin; dorsum of propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[160,241,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–79" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,495,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-164@17.[151,1436,489,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 71–79. Meria sanguinicollis, 71, 73, 76–77, ♀; 72, 74–75, 78–79, ♂. 71–72. Habitus, dorsal view; 73. Head, frontal view; 74. Head, ventral view; 75. Pronotum, lateral view; 76. Propodeum, dorsal view; 77. Metasoma, dorsal view; 78. T3–T5, dorsal view; 79. T7, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646969/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">Fig. 76</figureCitation>
) largely smooth, laterally and upper portion of side with dense striae; T1 (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1153,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–79" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,495,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-164@17.[151,1436,489,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 71–79. Meria sanguinicollis, 71, 73, 76–77, ♀; 72, 74–75, 78–79, ♂. 71–72. Habitus, dorsal view; 73. Head, frontal view; 74. Head, ventral view; 75. Pronotum, lateral view; 76. Propodeum, dorsal view; 77. Metasoma, dorsal view; 78. T3–T5, dorsal view; 79. T7, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646969/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
) subapically with a complete row of punctures forming complete groove; each of T2–T5 subapically with a row of punctures and medially a bit absent forming almost complete groove; T2–T4 (
<figureCitation box="[756,837,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–79" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,495,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-164@17.[151,1436,489,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 71–79. Meria sanguinicollis, 71, 73, 76–77, ♀; 72, 74–75, 78–79, ♂. 71–72. Habitus, dorsal view; 73. Head, frontal view; 74. Head, ventral view; 75. Pronotum, lateral view; 76. Propodeum, dorsal view; 77. Metasoma, dorsal view; 78. T3–T5, dorsal view; 79. T7, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646969/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
) laterally with small light spots, the distance between two lateral spots more than the length of the spot.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646969" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6646969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646969/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="169" startId="17.[151,264,1773,1797]" targetBox="[151,1435,495,1750]" targetPageId="17">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1773,1869]" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,340,1773,1797]" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">FIGURES 71–79.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morawitz" authorityYear="1893" box="[345,555,1773,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Meria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinicollis">
<emphasis box="[345,555,1773,1797]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">Meria sanguinicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 71, 73, 76–77, 
<specimenCount box="[718,738,1774,1797]" pageId="17" pageNumber="169" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
; 72, 74–75, 78–79, 
<specimenCount box="[938,960,1774,1797]" pageId="17" pageNumber="169" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
. 71–72. Habitus, dorsal view; 73. Head, frontal view; 74. Head, ventral view; 75. Pronotum, lateral view; 76. Propodeum, dorsal view; 77. Metasoma, dorsal view; 78. T3–T5, dorsal view; 79. T7, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1915,2014]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1436,150,286]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="170" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">
Male (
<figureCitation box="[271,355,1915,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–79" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,495,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-164@17.[151,1436,489,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 71–79. Meria sanguinicollis, 71, 73, 76–77, ♀; 72, 74–75, 78–79, ♂. 71–72. Habitus, dorsal view; 73. Head, frontal view; 74. Head, ventral view; 75. Pronotum, lateral view; 76. Propodeum, dorsal view; 77. Metasoma, dorsal view; 78. T3–T5, dorsal view; 79. T7, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646969/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
). Clypeus with moderate to sparse punctures; vertex with deep and moderate to sparse punctures, POD 1.1× OOD; pronotal transverse carina present but medially minutely absent, dorsum of pronotum moderately to sparsely punctate; lateral side of pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[663,743,1987,2014]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–79" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,495,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-164@17.[151,1436,489,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 71–79. Meria sanguinicollis, 71, 73, 76–77, ♀; 72, 74–75, 78–79, ♂. 71–72. Habitus, dorsal view; 73. Head, frontal view; 74. Head, ventral view; 75. Pronotum, lateral view; 76. Propodeum, dorsal view; 77. Metasoma, dorsal view; 78. T3–T5, dorsal view; 79. T7, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646969/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="169">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
) ventrally densely strio-punctate; ventral surface of mid femur smooth, without punctures nor setae; each of T1–T6 with apically yellowish band; two-thirds of T3–T5 (
<figureCitation box="[1345,1428,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–79" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,495,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-164@17.[151,1436,489,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 71–79. Meria sanguinicollis, 71, 73, 76–77, ♀; 72, 74–75, 78–79, ♂. 71–72. Habitus, dorsal view; 73. Head, frontal view; 74. Head, ventral view; 75. Pronotum, lateral view; 76. Propodeum, dorsal view; 77. Metasoma, dorsal view; 78. T3–T5, dorsal view; 79. T7, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646969/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="170">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
) basally with dense punctures and apical one-third smooth and impunctate; T7 (
<figureCitation box="[1042,1124,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–79" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,495,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-164@17.[151,1436,489,1750]" captionText="FIGURES 71–79. Meria sanguinicollis, 71, 73, 76–77, ♀; 72, 74–75, 78–79, ♂. 71–72. Habitus, dorsal view; 73. Head, frontal view; 74. Head, ventral view; 75. Pronotum, lateral view; 76. Propodeum, dorsal view; 77. Metasoma, dorsal view; 78. T3–T5, dorsal view; 79. T7, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646969/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="170">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
) moderately punctate, apex with deep notch and tipped lobes pointed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1087,258,286]" pageId="18" pageNumber="170" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,150,286]" box="[199,1087,258,286]" pageId="18" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,258,284]" pageId="18" pageNumber="170">Distribution.</emphasis>
